b'@chefdaniellambert is back in the kitchen :man_cook:This time showing us how to make a mouth-watering Smoked Bacon & Chorizo Risotto :drooling_face::drooling_face:

Ingredients:
Salt
Cracked Black Pepper
200g SuperValu Smoked Bacon Lardons
200g SuperValu Chorizo Sausage
500g Arborio Rice
1 Litre Vegetable Stock
200ml Red Wine
50ml SuperValu Red Wine Vinegar
30g SuperValu Applewood Cheddar
30g SuperValu Signature Tastes Parmesan
3 Tbls Fresh Chives
2 Sweet Onions
3 Purple Garlic Cloves
2 Cans SuperValu Italian Tomatoes
1tbls Tomato Paste
1 tbls Granulated Sugar
50ml SuperValu Balsamic Vinegar
SuperValu Extra Virgin Olive Oil
 
Method: For The Tomato Sauce:
Dice up 1 sweet onion, 1 purple garlic clove (or paste).

Turn pot up to full heat and a drizzle of extra virgin olive oil & add in your onions and garlic.

Sweat them off for 1 minute then add 2 cans of your Italian tomatoes , 50ml of balsamic vinegar, 1 table spoon of granulated sugar and 1 table spoon of tomato paste.

Let this simmer for 10 mins then blitz with a hand blender and set aside.
 
For the Risotto:
Dice up 1 sweet onion, 1 purple garlic clove (or paste), 200g of chorizo and smoked bacon lardons.

Turn up your pan to high heat, add a drizzle of extra virgin olive oil & add in your sweet onions, garlic, chorizo and bacon. 

Then add in 500g of Arborio rice.
If you need to add in more olive oil do. You want to sweat off these ingredients together until the rice starts to give a nutty smell (usually takes about 7-8 mins).

Start adding in ladles of your hot veg stock, very slowly and keep adding them until the tips of the risotto turn translucent (clear). This process usually takes about 15 \xe2\x80\x93 20 mins on a low to medium heat.

Pour in your hot tomato sauce & cover the risotto with the sauce. Mix & cook for a further 5 mins. 

Add in some cracked black pepper.

Grate 30g of applewood cheddar, 30g parmesan, and finely chop 2 table spoons of fresh chives, turn off the heat completely from your pan and add in your cheeses and chives.

Garnish with more parmesan & crispy chorizo if you wish, sit back and enjoy!'

b"Today's recipe of the day is Clonakilty Whitepudding Falafel by @jenniferocooks that features in The Clonakilty Black and White Cookbook. Super easy to make and packed full of flavour. We can't wait to tuck in. :sparkles: Find the @clonakilty_blackpudding recipe below.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Makes 8 | Cook Time: 7 \xe2\x80\x93 10 mins :fork_and_knife:
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients: \xe2\x81\xa3100g Clonakilty White Pudding \xe2\x81\xa3100g Sweet Potato (grated)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Garlic clove (minced)
\xe2\x81\xa31 spring onion (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3Pinch of chilli powder \xe2\x81\xa31 tsp of oil for frying \xe2\x81\xa3Sea Salt & Freshly ground black pepper to taste
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method
\xe2\x81\xa31.Add the grated sweet potato into a large mixing bowl, break the Clonakilty white pudding into small pieces and add to the bowl along with garlic, chili powder, spring onion, salt and pepper. \xe2\x81\xa32.Mix ingredients together gently until all ingredients are combined. \xe2\x81\xa33.Form the falafel shapes in the palms of your hands, place them on a flat plate and chill for half an hour in the fridge.
\xe2\x81\xa34.Heat a frying pan, add oil to pan, cook falafels for 7 \xe2\x80\x93 10 minutes over a medium heat turning to brown all sides. Serve immediately
\xe2\x81\xa35.Serving suggestion: Flatbreads, crunchy salad and tahini dressing.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ClonakiltyPudding #Clonakilty #falafels #ClonakiltyWhitePudding #IrishFood #ClonakiltyCreations"

b"Master the best brunch at home :white_heavy_check_mark:
\xe2\x81\xa3We are here to help you tick off all those cooking skills you want to perfect. Today we are sharing Kevin Dundon's easy-to-follow recipe for a super tasty brunch. (Looks impressive and it is easy to make. Win, win). :face_savoring_food:
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe for Sweet Potato Hash Browns with Poached Eggs & Asparagus \xe2\x81\xa3by @KevinDundon below or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Serves 4
\xe2\x81\xa3Prep Time: 10 minutes
\xe2\x81\xa3Cook Time: 15 minutes \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa33 handfull Baby Greens
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Balsamic Vinegar
\xe2\x81\xa350ml Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 - Onion (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Pinch Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa31 Pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa312 Asparagus
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Fresh Thyme
\xe2\x81\xa34 - SuperValu Signature Tastes Corn Fed Hen Eggs
\xe2\x81\xa3100 g SuperValu Signature Tastes Parma Ham
\xe2\x81\xa32 - Sweet Potatoes (peeled)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp White Vinegar
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 180\xc2\xb0C. \xe2\x81\xa32. Grate the sweet potatoes into a large bowl. Add the onion, thyme, tablespoon of flour and season with salt and pepper.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Combine and shape into four patties. \xe2\x81\xa34. Wrap the asparagus in the parma ham and place on a roasting tray. \xe2\x81\xa3Heat the oil in a frying pan. Over low heat add the patties and cook for four minutes until golden brown at the edges. \xe2\x81\xa35. Flip with a fish slice and continue cooking for a further five to seven minutes, depending on the thickness of the hash browns. \xe2\x81\xa36. Place the asparagus in the oven and roast for 10 minutes until coloured. \xe2\x81\xa3Meanwhile, prepare the poached eggs. Working with one or two eggs at a time, crack each egg into separate ramekins.
\xe2\x81\xa37. Add vinegar to a saucepan filled with water. Bring to the boil over medium-high 8. heat. Once the water boils, reduce heat to low-medium (the water should be just simmering with small bubbles rising from the base of the pan). \xe2\x81\xa39. Using a whisk, stir the water in one direction to create a whirlpool. Slide the egg from saucer into the centre of the whirlpool and simmer for three or four minutes, without stirring. \xe2\x81\xa310. Lift the egg onto a clean towel to drain. \xe2\x81\xa311. Serve each hash brown with a poached egg, some crispy parma asparagus and a few salad leaves drizzled with balsamic vinegar. \xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #Brunch."

b":white_medium_star::white_medium_star::white_medium_star::white_medium_star:
\xe2\x81\xa3@kevindundon's Chocolate Biscuit Cake recipe is one of our most highly reviewed recipes on our website and it always sparks a debate over the addition of cherries. :cherries:What do you add to your biscuit cake? We know lots of you love making it for birthday celebrations. :partying_face: Tag someone who you think should make it :winking_face_with_tongue:
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3225g Digestive Biscuits (Rich Tea/Digestive/Chocolate)
\xe2\x81\xa3110 g Glace Cherries (optional)
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Golden Syrup
\xe2\x81\xa375g Malteasers
\xe2\x81\xa3110g Mini Marshmallows
\xe2\x81\xa3110g Butter
\xe2\x81\xa3100ml Cream
\xe2\x81\xa3325g Dark Chocolate (broken into chunks)
\xe2\x81\xa3110g Milk Chocolate
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Line an eight inch/23cm square cake tin with a double layer of cling film or parchment paper.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Place the butter, chocolate and golden syrup into a large bowl and place over a saucepan of simmering water.
\xe2\x81\xa33. When the chocolate mixture has thoroughly melted, add in the biscuits, malteasers, cherries and mix well.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Pour the chocolate and biscuit mixture into the lined cake tin and stick the mini marshmallows into the top in a haphazard fashion.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Transfer to the fridge and allow to set.
\xe2\x81\xa36. When set prepare the ganache.
\xe2\x81\xa37. In a saucepan, bring cream to the boil. Remove from the heat and add the leftover 100g dark chocolate. Stir until smooth and pour over biscuit cake.
\xe2\x81\xa38. Decorate with more marshmallows and let set for two hours more if you can. \xe2\x81\xa39. Cut into small portions and enjoy within a week! \xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #Recipeoftheday"

b'Our simple recipe for Sweet Potato, Chickpea & Spinach Jalfrezi Curry is so easy to make and is absolutely delicious :face_savoring_food: Time to dig out all the spices from your cupboard and rustle up this super tasty dish. Tag us using #SuperValu or @SuperValu_irl so we can see your take on our curry recipe. \xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the below or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Chickpeas (drained and rinsed)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Chilli Powder
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Chopped Tomatoes
\xe2\x81\xa34 cloves Garlic
\xe2\x81\xa30.5 tsp Ground Cinnamon
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Ground Coriander
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Ground Cumin
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Ground Turmeric
\xe2\x81\xa31 Lime (cut into wedges, to serve. Optional)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 Onion (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa350g Baby Spinach
\xe2\x81\xa31 Piece Fresh Ginger (thumb-sized piece, peeled and finely grated)
\xe2\x81\xa32 Medium Sweet Potato (peeled and cubed)
\xe2\x81\xa325g Toasted Almond Flakes (to garnish. Optional)
\xe2\x81\xa3500ml Vegetable Stock
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Heat the oil in a large saut\xc3\xa9 pan set over a low to medium heat. Add the onion, garlic and ginger and saut\xc3\xa9 for 6 to 8 minutes, until softened. Stir in the spices and some salt and pepper and fry for a minute or two.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Add the chopped tomatoes, sweet potatoes and stock. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes, until the sweet potatoes are tender and the sauce has slightly reduced. Add the chickpeas and spinach and allow the spinach to wilt.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Ladle the curry into bowls. Scatter over the flaked almonds and serve with a lime wedge on the side.
\xe2\x81\xa3Tip - This curry tastes delicious for a few days and keeps well, so it\xe2\x80\x99s an ideal meal for making ahead or having for lunch the next day. It even tastes great cold!
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #Recipeoftheday'

b'These quick and easy vegetable fajitas are perfect for the whole family as everyone can assemble their own and include the toppings they like such as salsa or cheese! You could also add diced chicken, beef or pork to this recipe. :mobile_phone_with_arrow: Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa32 cloves Garlic
\xe2\x81\xa3chopped
\xe2\x81\xa32 Green Pepper (sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa3225g Mushrooms (sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa32 medium Onions (sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa32 Red Pepper (sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Fresh Coriander (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa32 Green Chilli (deseeded and sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Oil
\xe2\x81\xa312 Whole Wheat Tortilla
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Warm the oil in a large frying pan set over a low heat. Add the onions and garlic and cook for 5 minutes, until soft. Stir in the green and red peppers, chillies and coriander and cook for 10 minutes.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Meanwhile, heat the tortillas according to the packet instructions.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Add the mushrooms to the pan and cook for 1 minute. Season to taste and divide the vegetables between the tortillas, then roll up and serve.
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #thereforyou #Recipe'

b'You only need five ingredients for our super simple & tasty Potato Cakes :potato:
\xe2\x81\xa3Potato cakes are absolutely delicious and a great way of using up some leftover mashed potatoes. You can add in whatever you wish in terms of fish, leftover bacon or chicken.:face_savoring_food: If you try this recipe at home be sure to tag us in your creations using #SuperValu :mobile_phone_with_arrow: Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 Egg
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Parsley (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3700g Potatoes
\xe2\x81\xa34 stems Scallions (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3150g Smoked Bacon Lardons
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Mix all the ingredients together until well combined.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Season lightly with a little black pepper.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Divide into eight shapes and then mould into little patties.
\xe2\x81\xa34. I normally, and if time allows, arrange them on a plate at this stage and transfer them to the fridge for at least 1 hour.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Meanwhile heat a large pan with a little butter.
\xe2\x81\xa36. Cook the potato cakes on both sides until they are golden brown.
\xe2\x81\xa37. Make sure they are really well heated through-if you are a little concerned about them you could transfer them into the oven for a few minutes to ensure that they are really well heated through.
\xe2\x81\xa38. Serve with a large salad and/or a softly poached egg. Simply Delicious!
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #thereforyou'

b'Almond Butter Chocolate Cups that are perfect for making at home. If you give the recipe a try we would love to see your creation, tag us using #SuperValu.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3150g Dark Chocolate (roughly chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Honey
\xe2\x81\xa3100 g Milk Chocolate (roughly chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa3100g Smooth Almond Butter
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Seed Mix
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Icing Sugar
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Vanilla Extract
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Line a 12-cup muffin tin with paper or silicone cupcake cases.
\xe2\x81\xa32. In a small bowl, beat the almond butter, seeds, icing sugar, honey, vanilla extract and salt to combine.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Roll the mixture into 12 equalsized balls (about 12g each). Flatten each ball a little to a diameter that\xe2\x80\x99s slightly smaller than your muffin cases and freeze on the lined baking tray for 10 to 15 minutes while you prepare the chocolate.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Put the chocolate in a food processor. Blend until you get a mixture that resembles fine breadcrumbs. Scrape down the sides and bottom of the food processor with a spatula. Blend again until the chocolate clumps up into a ball, then break it up using your hands.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Blend again until you get a thick texture, like ganache. Scrape down the sides and bottom of the food processor. Keep blending until you get smooth, fluid chocolate. This may take 5 to 8 minutes.
\xe2\x81\xa36. Spoon 1 teaspoon of melted chocolate into the bottom of each cupcake case, swirling each one gently to ensure the chocolate reaches the edges.
\xe2\x81\xa37. Remove the almond butter discs from the freezer. Place one in each cupcake case, on top of the chocolate. \xe2\x81\xa38. Divide the remaining melted chocolate between the cases, about 2 teaspoons in each. Tap the tin so that the chocolate settles in an even layer. Sprinkle with cocoa nibs, if using, then leave to cool and harden at room temperature.
\xe2\x81\xa38. The cups will keep in an airtight container in the fridge for two weeks. Almond butter-choc cups made with tempered chocolate can be kept out of the fridge.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #thereforyou'

b"If you're looking for something new to try for breakfast our Very Berry Beetroot Smoothie is really quick to make and can be made using fresh or frozen fruit. You can find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio above. \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3375ml Coconut Water
\xe2\x81\xa31 - 2 tbsp Honey
\xe2\x81\xa35  Ice Cubes
\xe2\x81\xa3Juice of half a Lime
\xe2\x81\xa320g Porridge Oats
\xe2\x81\xa31 Small Fresh Organic Raw Beetroot (roughly chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3100g Frozen Mixed Berries (such as strawberries, raspberries, blueberries and/or blackberries)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Flax Seed
\xe2\x81\xa31 Peach (or nectarine, stoned)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method: \xe2\x81\xa31. There's no need to peel the beetroot if you scrub it well. Simply place all the ingredients in a blender and blitz for 1 minute, until completely smooth and creamy. \xe2\x81\xa32.This can be made in advance and stored in the fridge overnight for a grab-and-go breakfast - just give it a stir before serving.
\xe2\x81\xa3

b'Coconut Chocolate Bars.:coconut::coconut: This healthier take on a Bounty Bar is a great pick-me-up or post-workout treat.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking on this link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa350 g Coconut Flour
\xe2\x81\xa3300 ml Coconut Milk
\xe2\x81\xa3200 g Dark Chocolate 70%
\xe2\x81\xa3150 g Desiccated Coconut
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Maple Syrup
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Put a wire cooling rack on a shallow baking tray.
\xe2\x81\xa32.Mix together the desiccated coconut, coconut flour, coconut milk and maple syrup in a large bowl. With wet hands, shape the mixture into bars and arrange them on the wire rack. Refrigerate for 1 hour or put in the freezer for 10 to 15 minutes, until set.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Break up 150g of the chocolate and put it into a microwave-safe bowl. Set the microwave at half power, then melt the chocolate in 30-second bursts to start with, then reducing to 10-second bursts, stirring between each burst until the chocolate is mostly melted but still with a few small chunks remaining. Remove the bowl from the microwave and stir in the remaining chocolate, square by square, stirring until the chocolate cools and thickens slightly.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Pour the chocolate over the bars on the wire rack, letting the excess drip down onto the baking tray. Put in the fridge, uncovered, until the chocolate has set.
\xe2\x81\xa3These bars will keep in an airtight container for up to a week in the fridge.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe'

b'Three words. CHOCOLATE....MUG...CAKE! Gimme, gimme, gimme! This is the ultimate baking cheat recipe. :chocolate_bar:Only a few ingredients needed and it is ready in a matter of minutes. Ideal for those late night chocolate cravings. \xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Cocoa Powder
\xe2\x81\xa31 Egg
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Milk
\xe2\x81\xa34 tbsp Self-Raising Flour
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Maple Syrup
\xe2\x81\xa320g Milk Chocolate
\xe2\x81\xa30.5 tsp Vanilla Extract
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Vegetable Oil
\xe2\x81\xa3Serve with SuperValu Signature Tastes Vanilla Spice Gelato for the perfect dessert. \xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. In a microwaveable mug, place all the flour and cocoa powder. Use the spoon to grind all of the cocoa and flour against the side of the mug so there are no lumps.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Add the egg and beat a little on top of the dry ingredients to break the yolk.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Add the oil, milk, vanilla and maple syrup. Mix until well combined.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Place the chocolate on a board and using a roller crush into small pieces. Stir into the mixture.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Put the mug into the microwave on high for 3 minutes. Leave to cool slightly before serving. Serve with some vanilla ice cream.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe'

b':honeybee:#SaveTheBees :honeybee:
\xe2\x81\xa3Did you know 1/3 of the food we eat is pollinated by bees; yet 30% of Irish bees are threatened by extinction? We at SuperValu don\xe2\x80\x99t want this to happen, which is why we have created the Save the Bees campaign! With the help of our school pollinator packs, we want to raise awareness of the importance of bees and show you the simple things you can do that will help save them!
\xe2\x81\xa3:honeybee::honeybee::honeybee::honeybee:
\xe2\x81\xa3For a strawberry flower to turn into a strawberry it needs to be visited five times by a bumblebee or 15 times by a honey bee. That\xe2\x80\x99s just for one strawberry! Apples need to be visited even more times. :strawberry::strawberry: Something to think about if you are having Kale Salad with Apple, Cranberries & Poached Eggs for lunch today. :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Bee sure to check out SuperValu.ie for everything you need to know about bees, pollination and what you can do to help!
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Recipe link in bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe'

b'Our recipe of the day Vegan Sausage & Bean Stew :green_heart: This substantial stew also works great as a burrito filling for a perfect midweek dinner. Tag someone who need some vegan dinner inspiration. :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down:or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Cannellini Beans (drained and rinsed)
\xe2\x81\xa3800g Chopped Tomatoes
\xe2\x81\xa32 cloves Garlic (thinly sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Kidney Beans (drained and rinsed)
\xe2\x81\xa36 Linda McCartney Vegan Sausages @lindamccartneyfoods
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Maple Syrup
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa31 Red Chilli (deseeded and finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Soy Sauce
\xe2\x81\xa31 bunch Fresh Coriander (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa380g Tomato Puree
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Put a medium-sized pan on a high heat. Once hot, add the oil and sausages and cook for about 3 minutes, until the sausages start to turn golden and char slightly.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Add all the remaining ingredients to the pan except the coriander. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for a couple of minutes. Taste and season with salt and pepper if you think it needs it, then stir in the coriander and ladle the stew into bowls.

b':police_car_light:New recipe alert :police_car_light: Courgette, Feta & Salmon Pasta Salad. \xe2\x81\xa3You can build the dish by adding chopped olives or diced shallots for extra texture and pan-frying the courgette ribbons in small batches will give them a crispier and greener feel. :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes:
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Balsamic Dressing
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa31 Lemon (zest and juice)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa34 Courgette (peeled into ribbons)
\xe2\x81\xa340g Feta Cheese (crumbled)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Fresh Chives (snipped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Fresh Mint (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Fresh Parsley Flat Leaf (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa34 Fresh Salmon Darnes
\xe2\x81\xa3500g Fusilli Pasta (or orzo or farfalle)
\xe2\x81\xa3200g Smoked Salmon (cut into bite-sized pieces)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Cook the pasta as per the packet instructions or until al dente. Drain and rinse under cold running water.
\xe2\x81\xa32. To poach the salmon, bring a small pot of salted water to the boil. Reduce the heat and add the salmon, then simmer for about 5 minutes, until the fish is cooked through. 3. Gently rinse the fish under cold running water, then set aside to cool.
\xe2\x81\xa3Brush the ridges of a griddle pan with oil and set over a high heat. Brush the courgette strips with oil too, then add them to the hot pan a few at a time and cook each side for 1 to 2 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl and season in between batches.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Add the pasta, feta cheese, herbs and lemon zest to the bowl, then drizzle with the lemon juice and dressing. Toss once or twice and check the seasoning. Flake in the poached salmon and add the smoked salmon too. Toss again until everything is evenly combined. Serve immediately.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #SuperValuLunchReicpes #SuperValuSaladRecipes'

b"Don't get stuck in a recipe rut. :woman_gesturing_NO_selector:Mix it up this week and try something new! How about Thai Chicken Cups? Or visit SuperValu.ie for hundreds of new recipes.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down:or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3200g Chicken Breast (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3125g Greek Yoghurt
\xe2\x81\xa31 Lime (zest and juice)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Rapeseed Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 small Red Onion (finely diced)
\xe2\x81\xa31 small Red Pepper (finely diced)
\xe2\x81\xa31 medium Carrot (grated)
\xe2\x81\xa31 handful Fresh Coriander (leaves, roughly chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa325g Goodness Cashew Nuts (crushed)
\xe2\x81\xa38 Little Gem Lettuce (leaves)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tsp Thai Red Curry Paste
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31.Warm the curry paste and oil in a large frying pan set over a medium heat. Add the chopped chicken and lime zest and fry for 10 minutes, until the chicken is light brown and cooked through. Remove from the heat and leave to cool.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Meanwhile, put the lime juice, yogurt and coriander in a large bowl and mix together well. Add the cooled cooked chicken to the bowl and stir to coat.
\xe2\x81\xa33. To assemble the cups, spoon the chicken into the lettuce leaves. Top with some onion, pepper and carrot and sprinkle with crushed cashew nuts.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #SuperValuLunchRecipes"

b"And just like that it's the 1st of March! Seriously... Where did February go? Start the month off right with our recipe for EPIC Moroccan Baked Eggs with Sausage Meatballs made with our award-winning SuperQuinn sausages. :face_savoring_food:
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Recipe link in bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa375 g Chorizo Sausages (cut into chunks)
\xe2\x81\xa34 Eggs
\xe2\x81\xa31 clove Garlic (grated)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Natural Yogurt
\xe2\x81\xa31 drop Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 Onion (halved and thinly sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Red Chilli (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Red Pepper (cut into 1cm strips)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa31 bunch Fresh Coriander (leaves, to garnish)
\xe2\x81\xa32 Pitta Breads
\xe2\x81\xa3600g Tomato Passata
\xe2\x81\xa36 Superquinn Award Winning Sausages
\xe2\x81\xa31.5 tsp Ground Cumin
\xe2\x81\xa31 Yellow Pepper (cut into 1cm strips) \xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 180C/gas mark 4.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Squeeze the meat from the sausage casings and roll into 2cm balls.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Set an ovenproof frying pan set over a medium heat. Add the chorizo and cook, turning, for 3 minutes or until browned. Using a slotted spoon, transfer to a plate lined with kitchen paper. Add the sausage pieces to the pan and cook, turning, for 3 minutes or until browned. Using a  slotted spoon, add to the chorizo to drain.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Add the onion and peppers to the same pan and cook, stirring frequently, for 6 minutes, until soft. Stir in the garlic, chilli and cumin and cook for 1 minute, then return the chorizo and sausages to the pan along with the tomato passata. Bring to a simmer, then cook for 5 minutes, until the sauce is slightly thickened. Season with salt and pepper.
\xe2\x81\xa35.Make 4 wells in the tomato sauce in each dish, then carefully crack an egg into each well. Transfer the pan to the oven for 10 minutes, until the egg whites are just set and the yolks are still runny.
\xe2\x81\xa36. Meanwhile, toast the pitta bread, then drizzle with a little oil and season with salt and pepper. \xe2\x81\xa3To serve, scatter the coriander leaves over the baked eggs, then drizzle with yogurt. Bring the pan straight to the table to let everyone help themselves and serve the toasted pitta bread on the side.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #SuperValuBreakfastRecipes"

b'Short on time in the evening but want to eat healthy? Hit the save button now!! Our quick and easy recipe for Asian Salmon & Noodle Parcels is delicious.
\xe2\x81\xa3Gluten free :white_heavy_check_mark: dairy free :white_heavy_check_mark: and easy to assemble :white_heavy_check_mark: It\xe2\x80\x99s an ideal make-ahead meal, which can be ready to put on to cook when you get in from your day.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down:or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3150 g Frozen Peas
\xe2\x81\xa3fresh can also be used
\xe2\x81\xa34 tbsp Light Soy Sauce
\xe2\x81\xa31 Lime (quartered)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Red Chilli (deseeded and finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 stick SuperValu Fresh Ginger (thumb sized, peeled and cut into thin matchsticks)
\xe2\x81\xa34 fillets Fresh Salmon Fillets (150g each)
\xe2\x81\xa34 Scallions (sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa3350g Thai Rice Noodles
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 200\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 6 or set a large steamer pan on to boil on the hob.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Place the noodles in a wide, shallow bowl or baking dish and pour over enough just-boiled water to cover. Leave to soak for about 3 minutes, until bendable but not cooked through.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Drain the noodles well and return to the bowl. Add the peas, spring onions, chilli (if using) and ginger.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Divide the noodle mixture evenly between four large squares of parchment paper. Sit a salmon fillet on top, followed by 1 tablespoon of soy sauce over each one. Gather the edges of parchment paper up over the salmon, scrunching them together to enclose securely. These can be prepared to this stage up to a day in advance and kept refrigerated. If being frozen, make sure you defrost them thoroughly before cooking.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Pop the parcels on a baking tray if baking in the oven or into the steamer tray covered with the lid if cooking on the hob. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes, until cooked through.
\xe2\x81\xa36. Place a parcel on each serving plate with a lime wedge and allow everyone to open their surprise meal themselves.
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Recipe link in bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #SuperValuDinnerRecipes'

b"Our recipe of the day is Oaty Cookie Strawberry 'Nice Cream' Sandwiches to celebrate #nationalstrawberryday :strawberry:Both the nice cream and cookies are gluten and refined sugar free, using only a little honey or maple syrup for sweetness making them a great treat for kids. \xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3For the Cookies
\xe2\x81\xa32 large Banana (about 325g)
\xe2\x81\xa350g Dried Apricots (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa30.5 tsp Ground Ginger
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Honey(or maple syrup)
\xe2\x81\xa3200g Rolled Oats (gluten-free if necessary)
\xe2\x81\xa350g Ground Almonds
\xe2\x81\xa350ml Sunflower Oil (or light-coloured olive oil, or melted coconut oil)
\xe2\x81\xa3For the Nice Cream
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Honey (or maple syrup)
\xe2\x81\xa375g Low Fat Natural Yogurt
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Strawberries (hulled and frozen)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 180\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 4. Line a large baking sheet with non-stick baking paper and set aside.
\xe2\x81\xa32. To make the cookies, peel the banana and mash in a large bowl. Add the apricots, oil, honey and ginger, blending them well. Add the oats and almonds and stir until well mixed. The mixture should stick together when squeezed.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Shape into 12 balls and flatten into cookies with a 7cm diameter, arranging them on the baking sheet as you go.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Bake in the oven for 25 minutes, until just firm and golden. Transfer to a wire rack and leave to cool completely.
\xe2\x81\xa35. To make the nice cream, place the frozen strawberries, yogurt and honey in a food processor or blender and blitz until really smooth. Blend for as little time as possible or it may become too soft. It should have an ice cream or frozen yogurt consistency and can be served straight away like this. However, for a firmer finish or if you\xe2\x80\x99re not ready to serve, transfer to a plastic container, cover and freeze.
\xe2\x81\xa36. To serve, sandwich a scoop of nice cream between two cookies and enjoy straight away.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #SuperValuDessertRecipes #GlutenFree"

b"Why not plan to meet your friend this weekend for that 'catch-up' you've been promising for so long? :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes: Tea + cake + chats = perfection. :carrot:Our Carrot & Parnsip Tray Bake with Cream Cheese & Maple Frosting by @sharonhearnesmith is sure to go down a treat. \xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa32 tsp Baking Powder
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Butter (for greasing)
\xe2\x81\xa32 medium Carrots (about 250g)
\xe2\x81\xa34 large Eggs
\xe2\x81\xa3200ml Light-Coloured Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa3280g Low Fat Cream Cheese
\xe2\x81\xa3225ml Maple Syrup
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Maple Syrup
\xe2\x81\xa34 tsp Mixed Spice
\xe2\x81\xa31 large Parsnips (about 250g)
\xe2\x81\xa375g Sultanas
\xe2\x81\xa3100g Walnuts (roughly chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3250g Wholemeal Flour
\xe2\x81\xa31 large Orange
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 180\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 4. Grease the base of a 20cm x 25cm baking tray or roasting tin that is also at least 5cm high and line with non-stick baking paper.
\xe2\x81\xa3Reserve 25g of the walnuts for decorating and pop the rest into a large bowl. Add the flour, sultanas, mixed spice and baking powder. Toss together well, make a well in the centre and set aside.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Measure the maple syrup into a large jug, followed by the olive oil. Beat in the eggs. Peel and roughly grate the carrots and parsnip and stir these through.
\xe2\x81\xa33.Pour the wet mixture into the dry ingredients and mix until well blended. Pour into the prepared tin and spread with the back of a spoon.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Bake in the oven for 35 minutes, until a skewer pierced into the centre of the tray bake comes out clean. Remove and leave to cool a little in the tin before lifting out and allowing to cool completely on a wire rack.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Meanwhile, to make the frosting, finely grate the orange zest and reserve it for decorating. Squeeze the juice into a bowl and add the cream cheese and maple syrup. 6. Mix until well blended. Cover and refrigerate until needed.
\xe2\x81\xa37. Spread the frosting evenly all over the top of the cooled cake. Scatter the reserved walnuts and orange zest over. Cut into 12 portions and serve.
\xe2\x81\xa3TIP - Use all parsnips without any carrot if preferred. Grated beetroot would work really well in this too.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #SuperValuBakingRecipes"

b'Our Oven-Baked Salmon with Chopped Orange is perfect for Ash Wednesday. :tangerine:Fish might not be the first thing that comes to mind as a roast dinner option, but this salmon dish is quick to make and is incredibly tasty. It goes perfectly with roast/steamed vegetables and sweet potatoes. \xe2\x81\xa3Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa32 cloves Garlic (crushed)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Ground Ginger
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Honey
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Fresh Parsley (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa34 Fresh Salmon Fillets
\xe2\x81\xa31 Orange (zest only)
\xe2\x81\xa34 slices of Orange
\xe2\x81\xa3150ml Orange Juice
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Tarragon (marjoram and/or thyme)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method: \xe2\x81\xa31. Place the salmon in a large baking dish and season with the tarragon, marjoram and/or thyme and a pinch of salt and pepper.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Mix the garlic, orange zest and juice, honey, olive oil and ginger together in a small bowl. Pour this on top of the salmon fillets and allow to marinate for 1 hour. Turn the salmon at least twice during this time in order to coat the salmon well with the marinade.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Preheat the oven to 200\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 6.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Top each fillet with an orange slice, then place the dish in the oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until the salmon is cooked through. Garnish with the chopped fresh parsley.
\xe2\x81\xa3*Serve with roast vegetables.
\xe2\x81\xa3Tip: Always cook your salmon fillet with the skin on, as leaving the skin intact helps the fillet hold together.'

b':pancakes::bear_face:Cuteness overload :pancakes::bear_face: Get creative on Pancake Tuesday & make their day extra special. Tag someone who would love this idea. \xe2\x81\xa3Find our recipe for classic & simple pancake batter below :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa32 - Eggs
\xe2\x81\xa3400 ml Milk
\xe2\x81\xa3250g Plain Flour
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Sunflower Oil (for frying)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method;
\xe2\x81\xa31. To make the pancake batter, sift the flour into a bowl, add the salt and make a well in the centre.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Break the eggs into the well and add a little of the milk.
\xe2\x81\xa3Gradually add the remaining milk into the egg and flour mixture using a large whisk until a smooth consistency has been achieved.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Cover with cling film and stand in the fridge for 1 hour if possible.
\xe2\x81\xa3Heat a heavy-based frying pan and when hot, brush with the minimum amount of oil.
\xe2\x81\xa3Pour a small amount of the batter onto the pan and swirl it around until it is evenly and thinly spread over the bottom.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Cook over a moderate to high heat for about 1 minute or until the edges are curling and the underside is golden.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Flip over and cook the second side for 30 seconds or so until golden.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.

b'For Friday night we are thinking Spaghetti with Prawns & Cherry Tomatoes, a glass of wine and of course GARLIC BREAD :raising_hands::raising_hands:What is your favourite weekend meal?
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below or by clicking the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa3300g Cherry Tomatoes (halved)
\xe2\x81\xa31 clove Garlic (sliced)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tbsp Red Wine Vinegar
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa36 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 Bunch Fresh Basil (shredded)
\xe2\x81\xa3300g Prawns (raw and peeled)
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Spaghetti
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3To serve
\xe2\x81\xa34 slices Crusty Bread
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Parmesan Cheese (grated)
\xe2\x81\xa3Or Garlic Bread
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method
\xe2\x81\xa31. Cook the pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water according to the packet instructions, until it\xe2\x80\x99s al dente. Drain and set aside.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Heat the oil in a large frying pan set over a medium heat. Add the prawns and garlic and cook for 2 to 3 minutes. Add the halved cherry tomatoes, basil and vinegar and the drained, cooked spaghetti. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper and mix everything together well.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Transfer to a large serving bowl and grate over some Parmesan. Set the bowl in the centre of the table and let everyone help themselves. Now all you need is some crusty bread and good company.
\xe2\x81\xa3.
\xe2\x81\xa3.

b'Our recipe of the day is SEAFOOD CHOWDER. A classic that is surprisingly easy to master. Hit the save button to find this recipe later and give it a go for yourself :smiling_face_with_smiling_eyes: \xe2\x81\xa3Recipe :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking on the link in our bio. \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 Head Broccoli (cut into florets)
\xe2\x81\xa33 large Carrots (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3500ml Full Fat Milk
\xe2\x81\xa32 Cloves Garlic (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31tsp Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 large Onion (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3500g Seafood (mix of cod, salmon and smoked haddock)
\xe2\x81\xa3150g Prawns (cooked)
\xe2\x81\xa32 Medium Sweet Potatoes (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Fresh Parsley (Chopped & used to garnish)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method;
\xe2\x81\xa31. Pour the milk into a saucepan and set over a medium heat. Add the fish mix and bring up to a steady simmer, then poach for 10 minutes. Strain the milk into a bowl and set the fish aside on a plate.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Heat the oil in a pot set over a medium heat, then fry the onion and garlic for 5 minutes. Add the carrots, sweet potatoes and broccoli and saut\xc3\xa9 for 5 minutes. Add the reserved milk and simmer for 25 minutes, until the sweet potatoes are soft. Add the poached fish and the prawns and simmer for 5 minutes more, until the seafood is heated through.
\xe2\x81\xa33. To serve, ladle into bowls and garnish with the chopped parsley.
\xe2\x81\xa3Tip: There\xe2\x80\x99s no question that cream makes chowder taste better, so if you don\xe2\x80\x99t mind the extra calories, then add in some double cream along with the milk. It will still be a super-nutritious meal, just a bit more energy dense.
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #Chowder'

b"Quick, healthy & versatile our Super Green Frittata recipe ticks all the boxes if you need dinner in a hurry. :white_heavy_check_mark:And it's great for using up veg you have in the fridge!
\xe2\x81\xa3Find the recipe below :backhand_index_pointing_down: or by clicking the link in the bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa33 Eggs (beaten)
\xe2\x81\xa31 clove Garlic (crushed)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Ground Cumin
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Paprika
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Rapeseed Oil
\xe2\x81\xa3Half a Red Onion (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3Half a Red Pepper (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa31 handful Baby Spinach
\xe2\x81\xa350g Feta Cheese (cubed, or grated mozzarella cheese)
\xe2\x81\xa31 handful Kale (roughly chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3Half a Yellow Pepper (finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 190\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 5.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Place an ovenproof non-stick frying pan on a high heat. Add the oil and swirl it to cover the base of the pan. Add the onion, peppers and garlic and cook for 2 minutes, then add the kale, spinach, paprika, cumin and a pinch of salt and pepper and cook for 2 minutes more.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Spread the ingredients evenly around the pan, then pour over the beaten eggs. Scatter the cheese on top and transfer to the oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until the egg is set and fully cooked.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Slide the frittata out of the pan onto a chopping board and cut into wedges to serve.
\xe2\x81\xa3Tip: If you like your food spicy, you can add some chopped fresh chilli or a pinch of chilli powder when seasoning your frittata. \xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe"

b'Think vol-au-vents are only for starters on Christmas Day think again.. Our Smoked Aubergine & Yogurt Vol-Au-Vents are perfect for parties any time of the year. :partying_face:
\xe2\x81\xa3Recipe below or in our bio :backhand_index_pointing_down:
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa31 Fresh Egg (beaten)
\xe2\x81\xa31 clove Garlic (crushed)
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Lemon Juice
\xe2\x81\xa3500ml Natural Yogurt (full-fat)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Sesame Seeds
\xe2\x81\xa36 Aubergines (small or medium)
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp SuperValu Fresh Parsley (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Pomegranate (seeds only)
\xe2\x81\xa38 Vol-au-vent Cases
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the grill to high.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Put the aubergines under the hot grill for 40 to 60 minutes, turning occasionally. Set aside until they\xe2\x80\x99re just cool enough to handle.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Once the aubergines come out of the oven, preheat the oven to 200\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 6.
\xe2\x81\xa34. While the aubergines are grilling, remove the vol-au-vents from the pack and brush with the beaten egg. Place in the refrigerator for 20 minutes.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Place the vol-au-vents on a baking tray and bake in the oven for 10 minutes, until risen and golden brown. Check underneath to make sure they are done. Peel off a layer of pastry from the centre to create a cavity and set the cases aside somewhere warm.
\xe2\x81\xa36. Make an incision along the centre of each still-hot aubergine and scoop out the flesh. Drain this in a colander, then chop and mix with the garlic, parsley, lemon juice and a pinch of salt and pepper.
\xe2\x81\xa37. To serve, spoon a generous amount of warm aubergine (reheated in a pan if necessary) into the vol-au-vents. Spoon some yogurt on top and swirl the two together a little. Scatter with pomegranate and sesame seeds, drizzle with a little olive oil and serve on a platter.
\xe2\x81\xa3'

b"Can you tell we're excited for pancake day. :pancakes: Our recipe of the day of Blueberry & Banana Pancakes and they're are goooooodddd :face_savoring_food::face_savoring_food::face_savoring_food:
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3Half a tbsp of Baking Powder
\xe2\x81\xa32 Bananas (very ripe & mashed)
\xe2\x81\xa32 Eggs
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Ground Cinnamon
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Milled Organic Flaxseed or chia seeds
\xe2\x81\xa3125g Blueberries
\xe2\x81\xa3100g Ground Almonds
\xe2\x81\xa31 drop of Oil (for cooking)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Honey (to serve)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Natural Yogurt (to serve)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Combine the mashed bananas and eggs in a large mixing bowl. Stir in the ground almonds, ground linseed, baking powder and cinnamon, then fold in the blueberries.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Heat a little oil in a frying pan set over a low heat. Spoon in some of the pancake batter and cook over a very low heat. Take your time and don\xe2\x80\x99t rush. When the pancakes are golden brown on the bottom, flip them over and cook the other side until golden brown.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Drizzle with honey and serve with natural yogurt."

b':sparkles:DINNER INSPIRATION:sparkles: Our recipe of the day is our incredible Tiger Prawn & Chickpea Curry. No need to order a takeaway when this is so tasty & easy to make :raising_hands::raising_hands:
\xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe below or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Chickpeas (drained and rinsed)
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Light Coconut Milk
\xe2\x81\xa31 Medium Onion (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3300g Basmati Rice (to serve)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Fresh Coriander leaves (to garnish)
\xe2\x81\xa350g Fresh Ginger (peeled and grated)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Bunch of Scallions (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3400g Tiger Prawns (raw fresh or frozen prawns, peeled)
\xe2\x81\xa32 tsp Thai Red Curry Paste
\xe2\x81\xa325 ml Vegetable Oil
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Heat the oil in a medium saucepan. Tip in the onion and ginger and cook for a few minutes, until softened. Stir in the curry paste and cook for 1 minute more. Add the tin of coconut milk, then half a tin of water. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add the prawns and chickpeas and cook for 5 to 7 minutes more, until the prawns are cooked and the chickpeas are heated through, then stir in the spring onions.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Serve with some cooked basmati rice and garnish with fresh coriander leaves.
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #Curry
\xe2\x81\xa3'

b':cooking:Our prosciutto-wrapped mini frittata tartlets are fantastic for both breakfast and lunch. If you make these once they are bound to become a weekly favourite! \xe2\x81\xa3:mobile_phone_with_arrow:Find the recipe by :backhand_index_pointing_right: @kevindundon below or by clicking on the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa34 Banana Shallots (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa324 Cherry Tomatoes (halved)
\xe2\x81\xa38 Large Eggs
\xe2\x81\xa31 Pack Filo Pastry (thawed)
\xe2\x81\xa34 Cloves Garlic (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Lemon (zest only)
\xe2\x81\xa360ml Milk
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Olive Oil (plus extra for greasing)
\xe2\x81\xa31 Pinch Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa31 Pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa3Half a head Cauliflower (cut into tiny florets)
\xe2\x81\xa33 tbsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa312 Slices Prosciutto
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Preheat the oven to 220\xc2\xb0C/gas mark 7. Lightly grease a 12-cup muffin tray.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Heat the olive oil in a frying pan set over a high heat. Add the cauliflower, shallots and garlic and saut\xc3\xa9 for 2 to 3 minutes, until softened, then season with the lemon zest and some salt and pepper. Remove from the heat, transfer to a bowl along with the cherry tomatoes and leave to cool.
\xe2\x81\xa33. In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs and milk and season with salt and pepper.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Unroll the filo pastry and cut into four equal square piles. Working with one sheet at a time, layer the filo pastry into each muffin cup, lightly brushing each sheet with the extra virgin olive oil. Once all the filo has been used up, add a slice of prosciutto as the final layer of the cup, leaving some of the ham hanging over the edge. Fill with the vegetable mixture, then pour the egg mixture into each tartlet and fold the prosciutto over the top.
\xe2\x81\xa35. Bake in the oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until the tartlets are set and cooked through with lovely crispy edges. Allow to cool on a wire rack for 5 minutes before removing from the tin. Serve warm.
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3#SuperValu #ItsGotToBe #Breakfast'

b'Our #Veganuary recipe of the day is this delicious :strawberry:KALE, BLUEBERRY AND STRAWBERRY SALAD:strawberry: It is giving us all the summer vibes :sun_selector: Find the simple recipe below or check out the link in our bio.
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Black Pepper
\xe2\x81\xa3Half a Lime (juice only)
\xe2\x81\xa31 pinch Salt
\xe2\x81\xa350g Blueberries
\xe2\x81\xa32 tsp Extra Virgin Olive Oil
\xe2\x81\xa325g Goodness Flaked Almonds
\xe2\x81\xa31 handful Kale (tough ribs removed and leaves finely chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp SuperValu Pine Nuts
\xe2\x81\xa36 Strawberries (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Toast the almonds and pine nuts in a hot dry pan for a few minutes, tossing regularly. Once they begin to brown, tip them out onto a plate.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Place the kale in a salad bowl, drizzle over the oil and massage it into the leaves. Add the lime juice and a pinch of salt and pepper and toss to coat the leaves with the juice and seasoning. Top with the blueberries, strawberries and nuts and serve straight away.

b'Easy Chocolate-Coated Caramel Bites :chocolate_bar: These super-tasty snacks are high in fibre and really easy to make. They will keep for at least two weeks in the fridge, but they will probably all be eaten long before then! :face_savoring_food:
\xe2\x81\xa3RECIPE \xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Cacao powder \xe2\x81\xa31 tbsp Coconut Oil \xe2\x81\xa3200g Dark Chocolate (chopped)
\xe2\x81\xa3100g Cashew Nuts \xe2\x81\xa3100g Walnuts \xe2\x81\xa3200g Medjool Dates (pitted)
\xe2\x81\xa31 tsp Vanilla Extract \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa31. Line a baking tray with non-stick baking paper.
\xe2\x81\xa32. Blend the walnuts and cashews in a food processor until they\xe2\x80\x99re like fine breadcrumbs. Add the dates, cacao powder, coconut oil and vanilla and blend until super-smooth, like toffee.
\xe2\x81\xa33. Using damp hands, roll the mixture into small balls. If you wet your hands with cold water, the caramel won\xe2\x80\x99t stick to your hands as much. Set aside.
\xe2\x81\xa3Melt the chocolate in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of simmering water or in the microwave.
\xe2\x81\xa34. Using two spoons, dip each caramel ball into the melted chocolate, making sure to completely coat each ball. Place on the lined baking tray and repeat with the remaining balls. Put in the fridge and leave the chocolate to harden. Once the chocolate has set, store the balls in an airtight container in the fridge for up to two weeks.

b':tangerine:Orange, carrot & ginger smoothie.:tangerine: Dietician @aveenbannon shares her simple recipe to kick start your new year. You only need four ingredients! \xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Ingredients:
\xe2\x81\xa32 oranges (peeled & pips removed)
\xe2\x81\xa32 carrots (cut into chunks)
\xe2\x81\xa33 slices of fresh ginger
\xe2\x81\xa32cm piece of fresh turmeric or half a teaspoon of ground turmeric
\xe2\x81\xa3
\xe2\x81\xa3Method:
\xe2\x81\xa3Place all the ingredients in a high-powered blender.
\xe2\x81\xa3Cover with cold water and a few ice cubes, if using, and blitz until smooth.
\xe2\x81\xa3Drink immediately.
